    implementation_delta: |
      Completed LNG-CORE-51: Function expressions (fn(params) => body) with closure capture.
      
      Changes made:
      1. Grammar (runtime/grammar_contract.py):
         - _fn() method parses 'fn' '(' params? ')' '=>' expr
         - call_suffix now works on arbitrary expressions (removed ident-only restriction)
         - Changed call node from callee (string) to target (expr) for arbitrary call targets
      
      2. AST (runtime/ast_contract.py):
         - 'fn' node with params (string array) and body (expr) already defined
         - Updated 'call' node: target is now expr (was ident string)
         - Updated validator to check target expression instead of callee ident
      
      3. Runtime (runtime/interpreter_runtime.py):
         - _eval handles 'fn' kind by creating Closure with captured environment
         - _eval handles 'call' kind by evaluating target, checking Closure, binding params
         - Closure properly captures lexical scope at definition point
      
      4. Tests (runtime/test_function_expressions.py):
         - Created 18 comprehensive tests covering all acceptance criteria
         - All 18 tests pass
         - Existing tests (let, if, object, list) all still pass
      
      Test coverage:
      - No-param functions: fn() => 42
      - Single/multi-param functions
      - Immediate invocation: (fn(x) => x * 2)(5) -> 10
      - Let-bound functions with calls
      - Closures with captured variables
      - Currying: fn(x) => fn(y) => x + y
      - Higher-order functions (functions in lists)
      - Error handling: E_RT_ARITY_MISMATCH for arg count mismatches
      - All 18 tests pass; existing tests for let/if/object/list all still pass
    tests:
      - runtime/test_function_expressions.py: 18/18 pass
      - runtime/test_let_expressions.py: 19/19 pass
      - runtime/test_if_expressions.py: 19/19 pass
      - runtime/test_object_literals.py: 14/14 pass
